               <head>Zikr al-siyar</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Z̲ikr al-siyar by Ghulām Ḥusayn Khān ibn Muḥammad Himmat Khān</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/n50002518 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115920 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85064914 http://lccn.loc.gov/n50063254" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3978-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f1205">Ghulām Ḥusayn Khān ibn Muḥammad Himmat Khān</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="person_f1205" type="supplied">غلام حسين خان ابن محمّد همّت خان</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_9238">Z̲ikr al-siyar</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_9238">ذكر السّير</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Abridged version of an earlier history of the same name covering the Timurid or Mughal
									Empire, from Nādir Shāh's sack of Delhi in 1151/1738-9 to
									the end of Emperor Shāh ʿĀlam's reign, in 1221 / 1806</p>
                        <p>The prose of this version simplifies the earlier rhetorical style</p>
                        <p>The title is an abjad-based tāʾrīkh (yielding 1221)</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>Transcribed by order of <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7663" role="fmo">G. J. Nicholls</persName>, Judge at <name type="place">Farrukhabad</name>, from a manuscript obtained from <name type="place">Agra</name>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
